Posted: Wed Apr 04, 2012 2:57 am
ronelson wrote:Quote:Yet he was still branded Kingslayer and had his honor questioned since then.I think his still wearing the white had something to do with that...This particular is--probably intentionally--the most amusing bit of absurd humour in the entire series. Everyone despised the Mad King and everyone despises his killer. The hypocrisy is so thick you could cut it with a knife. But it goes deeper than that.Here you have a feudal society, with the strongest conceivable implementation of "might makes right", but everyone crows about "honor" and "law" and "sworn oaths". Every asshole with an army to his name lays claim to the throne, and everyone else is impugning the legitimacy of their claim with one side of their mouth and with the other conceding that there is no justness to the whole affair to begin with and the strongest army will win in the end. "He's not the heir because incest!" "He's not the heir because I'm older!" "He's not the heir because I have more troops!" (At least Renly was honest.) "I want to secede because I don't like the Lannisters!" "I want the kingdom because I have dragons and long ago my forefather conquered your lands and somehow that gives me legitimacy!"The whole thing--popular opinion in the books in general and popular opinion on who is and is not honourable in particular--is a farce, and I can't see how it could be anything other than an intentional reflection of real life. And like in real life, with a farce of this magnitude you can sink in the depths of jaded impotent frustration, or you can laugh. I expect I'll be laughing my ass off by the time the series is done.In other news, Lady Olenna Tyrell makes a great first impression.
